{{ja-kanjitab|つみは|yomi=k}}
{{ja-kanjitab|つみば|yomi=k}}
{{IPAfont|⟨tumi<sub>1</sub> pa⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/tumipa/}} → {{IPAchar|/t͡sumifa/}} → {{IPAchar|/t͡sumiha/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=つみは|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (720 {{CE}}).

Appears to be derived from a compound. {{rfv-etymology|ja}}

Usually pronounced with {{rendaku|sort=つみば}}, as ''tsumiba''.

{{ja-noun|つみは|つみば}}

# the [[guard]] at the end of the grip of a [[sword]] or [[polearm]]
#* {{RQ:Wamyō Ruijushō|5|45}}<ref name="WMS">{{R:Wamyō Ruijushō}}</ref>
#*: {{lang|ja|'''鐔''' 唐韻云、鐔、音尋、一音潭、'''都美波''' [...] 今俗急呼都婆 劔鼻也}}

{{ja-kanjitab|つば|yomi=k}}
{{IPAchar|/tumiha/}} → {{IPAchar|/tumuba/}} → {{IPAchar|/tunba/}} → {{IPAchar|/t͡suba/}}

Likely from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=つば|-}}, attested in the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' (938 {{CE}}).

Shift from ''tsumiha'' or ''tsumiba'' above.

{{ja-noun|つば}}

# the [[guard]] at the end of the grip of a [[sword]] or [[polearm]]
#* {{RQ:Wamyō Ruijushō|5|45}}<ref name="WMS"/>
#*: {{lang|ja|'''鐔''' 唐韻云、鐔、音尋、一音潭、都美波 [...] 今俗急呼'''都婆''' 劔鼻也}}
#* {{RQ:Nippo Jisho|620}}<ref name="NJ">{{R:Nippo Jisho}}</ref>
#*: {{lang|ja|'''Tçuba'''. '''ツバ''' ('''鍔'''・'''鐔''') 刀 (Catana)の鍔, すなわち, 刀の柄（つか）に密着している, 銅やその他の金属製の円いある種の輪.}}
# the [[brim]] or [[visor]] {{gloss|of a [[hat]], for example}}
# the [[brim]] of a [[kettle]]

